Very sweet hotel
This is a very sweet hotel. It’s small. It doesn’t have many guests in here, so the staffs will remember all the guests. It has some little inserts in the room but it didn’t affect my experience. I love here very much. Very good environment and polite staff. The room is very comfortable. I have a good sleep in here. They have many TV channel in here too. You’ll never feel bored😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍
Thống Huynh wrote a review Jul 2019
Da Nang, Vietnam3 contributions3 helpful votes
Awesome place
Upon arrival at Minh House, I was greeted with the warmest welcome I have ever experienced. The staff Kelvin was there to greet me and made sure I had everything I needed, including help with planning my stay in Da Nang and even sent his colleague to accompany me sightseeing since I was traveling solo. The room was clean and spacious and the hotel is located very close to the beach. It was great to be able to walk there in the AM before departing from Da Nang. Highly recommended for anyone visiting Da Nang. Big thanks to Kelvin and all staffs in Minh hotel
Bazzathegreat wrote a review Jul 2019
Avoca Beach, Australia119 contributions101 helpful votes
Not bad but!
Hotel looks great on the web. We had a number of issues . The floor tiles in the bathroom and around the pool are very slippery. No where to hang towels.The A/c didn’t cool the room down to 20c. There is no room around the pool to put sun lounger. The breakfast was very average- cold tea and coffee, processed spam and eggs you could bounce off the wall. Staff were nice ,however wouldn’t go back.
2 Helpful votes
micttda130015 wrote a review Jun 2019
awsome hotel
The service in this hotel is execellent, very friendly staff esp Kelvin. The hotel is just a few hundred meters to the beach but still in a quiet street. Many other bars and restaurants and massage are just around the corner.
Date of stay: May 2019
